description: Template for datasets reporting protein-protein interaction measurements such as affinity purification mass spectrometry, BioID proximity labeling, or yeast two-hybrid screens.

baitProtein.description: Protein identifier or name of the bait used for interaction detection experiments.
baitProtein.title: baitProtein

baitGene.description: Gene symbol associated with the bait protein.
baitGene.title: baitGene

interactionDetectionMethod.description: Method or platform used to detect protein interactions (e.g., AP-MS, BioID, yeast two-hybrid).
interactionDetectionMethod.title: interactionDetectionMethod

interactionScore.description: Quantitative confidence or interaction score reported for the protein interaction (e.g., SAINT score, % control).
interactionScore.title: interactionScore

interactionScoreType.description: Label describing the scoring metric used for the interaction measurement.
interactionScoreType.title: interactionScoreType

age.description: A numeric value representing age of the individual. Use with `ageUnit`.
age.title: age

aliquotID.description: A unique identifier (non-PII) that represents the aliquots used for e.g. replicate runs. This is linked to the specimenID.
aliquotID.title: aliquotID

individualID.description: A unique identifier (non-PII) that represents the individual from which the data came. This could be a patient or animal ID.

modelSex.description: Sex of the individual animal model used in the experiment. Distinct from donor sex.
modelSex.title: modelSex
